# agent-os schema (Cursor)

This project uses the agent-os pattern. Read these at session start:

- @AGENTS.md — thin stub, points to the full schema
- @agent/AGENTS.md — canonical schema (memory protocol, agent dispatch, rules table)
- @agent/memory/STATE.md — current priorities and blockers
- @agent/memory/learnings/mistakes.md — past mistakes (don't repeat) and patterns

Then, based on the task, read on demand:

- @agent/memory/wiki/INDEX.md → relevant wiki pages
- @agent/memory/projects/*.md if a client task
- @agent/rules/<rule>.md when behavior is in question

Do not duplicate the schema content here. agent/AGENTS.md is the source of truth.

When in doubt about how to behave: read agent/AGENTS.md first.
